REGION

A model for a lockable and dirtyable region of a file channel.

    Issues and Tasks: http://blogometer.com/trac/incubator
    Source: http://github.com/bigeasy/region/tree/master
    Contact: alan@blogometer.com

PURPOSE

Region associates a file position and a lock to a byte buffer. A region will
also track which bytes in the byte buffer are dirty and need to be written to
disk.

MOTIVATION

This came about when wanting a create a generic file header, so I wouldn't have
to sum field offsets.
